docs.name: Economic Policy Uncertainty - US Monthly Index Components
docs.description:
Policy-Related Economic Uncertainty Index is measured by using three types of underlying components. One component quantifies newspaper coverage of policy-related economic uncertainty. A second component reflects the number of 
federal tax code provisions set to expire in future years. The third component uses disagreement among economic forecasters as a proxy for uncertainty. For more details please visit 
the original source : Scott Baker, Nicholas Bloom and Steven J. Davis at www.PolicyUncertainty.com.

docs.name: Economic Policy Uncertainty - Europe Monthly Main Index
docs.description:
European policy-related economic uncertainty is measured by using two types of underlying components. 
One component quantifies newspaper coverage of policy-related economic uncertainty. 
A second component uses disagreement among economic forecasters as a proxy for uncertainty. For more details please visit 
the original source : Scott Baker, Nicholas Bloom and Steven J. Davis at www.PolicyUncertainty.com.

docs.name: Economic Policy Uncertainty - Canada Monthly Main Index
docs.description:
Canadian policy-related economic uncertainty is measured by using two types of underlying components. 
One component quantifies newspaper coverage of policy-related economic uncertainty. 
A second component uses disagreement among economic forecasters as a proxy for uncertainty.
For more details please visit the original source : Scott Baker, Nicholas Bloom and Steven J. Davis at www.PolicyUncertainty.com.
